values: well, sunday night was horrid. i absolutely could not sleep after my fucking roommate turned the light on when he came in at 2:30 in the morning. i was so hot and nervous, and had fitful sleep. i finally did fall asleep at like 6, so i slept until almost noon, which is really unlike me. after that, i got up and went to fred meyer's. i camped next to the starbucks and deli, hitting both of them up as i studied. i learned a lot, and felt really good about proofs up til that point. then i went back to WWU. after a short break, i started studying again, and it was HARD. so i looked up last year's tests, and had no fucking clue what the hell they were about. i studied and studied and went to bed at midnight. the next morning-tuesday- i woke up at 659, by the vibration of my phone on unmentionable parts of my body. i got up and stared at my desk from across the room for 15 minutes before i decided to get up. i met eve at the fountain, and we went in. holy shit. the test was the hardest i have ever taken in my life. luckily, we can get partial credit, so i am hoping that i got the 60% i need to pass the class. there were 3 problems worth 10 points, plus 3 extra credit problems worth three each. i basically got one right, so i got like 8-9. the other two i got prolly a 5 and a 2 on. that gives me 15 points. i needed 18 to get a 60%. so i am really hoping there are 3 points for me in the extra credit section. it took forever, but i may have passed. after that, i went to study spanish, which went really well, cause i know most of it well anyways. then kacie and i went to lunch. my test was at 1, and we got started right away. the 9 page test took me 40 minutes, so it wasn't really that bad. the subjunctive was difficult, but whatever. the hardest part was just rewriting a paragraph in the past tense, but that was just a lot of time without being difficult. kacie and i went to dinner, then i went back to my room and cleaned. when i was done except for laundry, kacie came over with hot chocolate, which i thought was the nicest thing ever. i invited her to stay, but it was almost 9, so she was going to talk to kevin. when he didnt call, she came over, and we watched laguna beach and most of real world. kevin finally called, and he had still been at the basketball games, because apparently JV went into 5 overtimes, bumping back the varsity. this morning i woke up to kacie calling, but it was a good thing i got up, because i didnt want to oversleep after a perfect night of sleep. i did some logic, then we went to lunch. i came back and did more logic, then she called to see if i wanted to go to target. we did, and then we went to haggen and fred meyer's so i could but scratch tickets. i won 9 bucks, then lost all of my 12. i am retarded. then i went to work on logic with eve, and cyd came along, but i am doing this instead- so that's how logics going..... ;)

well, today was delightfully boring in general. I woke up (basically) to a call from allie, letting me know that she wanted to get together and practice our skit for spanish- which is worth 10% of our grade. we practiced for a bit, then i went to lunch. rather than going to math, i stayed in my room and "studied" my lines. we got there, set up, and did a pretty darn good job, and the teacher kept telling us that, so that was good. after that, i watched the news, started my RA application, tried to quit my job, and then cleaned the shit out of and reorganized my room and bathroom. it is much better now. then i went to dinner, and now i am here. later, i plan on watching west wing, then going to dinner, coming back and studying. obviously, i need my daily dose of ann coulter's witty banter, then i will try and sleep. in the morning, i will brush up on current events, then run about 18 miles. (obviously am complete lazy lying bastard. will really wake up too late, maybe study, and then go in to take the quiz, and find out how i did on my exam.) then we get to see all of the rest of the skits, and then i am basically done with classes. we have a review day in math also, so all is good. i will see my adam one more time, and then probably never again, with my luck. damn.

Goodness me! Looking back now, all that seems so long ago. Since then, I have graduate High School, been to Boston, DC, New York, Atlanta, Montreal, moved into college, etc, etc. I'm at Western, which I guess would be a super place, but I have realized (epiphany!) that I am not meant for institutionalized education and vice versa. I learn much better on my own, and I have found that college is difficult, not as far as subject matter, but personally. I detest classes and teachers and assignments and all of that. While I have never been a counter culture alternative type, I have found that the system doesn't work. Now I am lazy and apathetic towards schoolwork, while I put amazing energy into extracurricular learning. Right now, I am trying to learn Japanese, with the help of my Japanese roommate. Anywho. I am still lusting after Jake, and Brandon, and there is this kid named Adam Summer I would kill for in my math class. Beautiful. Right, forgot. There was that little election. FUCK YES! I won. Rather, George Bush won, much to the chagrin of Rather. ha! Am v. witty and intelligent. Now that I am on here again, will post more often.

So, today I took the AP World History Exam. Holy Shit, Holy Shit, Holy Shit! I didn't remember how boring that was from the last one I took. The multiple choice was fairly easy, but the essays were harder. In recent news, I am friends again with my ex-best friend, I have been studying my ass off, and my best friend slept with my love interest. (Lust interest???) I cannot even imagine why I like this kid, him being straight, white trash, and fairly mean. It is only 19 days until I am 18, and I am so incredibly excited. At present, I don't know what the hell I am doing, however. I think my grades were incredibly shitty, for me at least. I have been just so excited.nervous.angry.sad.gleeful.oblivious.stressed. lately, that I cannot concentrate on pretty much anything. This AP thing was a big change, having to study so much, but I did read about 300 pages in two days of a delightfuly dry, inhuman textbook to study, so how is my concentration now, eh? If I could only see where my life was headed, I think I would be able to actually care about school. As of right now, all I want to do is go to college and study overseas, then have a job in which I can travel extensively, have a position of authority, and learn about languages and cultures. I have seriously been considering joining the Peace Corps, then maybe going to work for the diplomatic corps or some other government agency, although I don't know. Perhaps I could work in DC in the White House or other government body. Life is so confusing now, and it doesn't help to lose a best friend for months, love a straight boy, have that boy and ur best friend hook up and hear from someone else, and to be a gay jewish kid. Christ on a cracker when does this get easier? But I think I am truly the happiest right now, because of the people I love and have around me. I am so glad for Kate, Kortney, Ashlee, Rachel, Ann, Felicia, Jackie, Jake even though i hate him right now and vice versa, my family, and my other friends. PS Cancun is where all the hot guys live, I found them! ! ! ! ! ! YAY -Trevor-
